{"metadata":{"symbolKind":"method","role":"symbol","title":"wait(mutex:)","externalID":"s:4GLib12CondProtocolPAAE4wait5mutexyqd___tAA05MutexC0Rd__lF::SYNTHESIZED::s:4GLib4CondC","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"wait"},{"text":"<","kind":"text"},{"kind":"genericParameter","text":"MutexT"},{"kind":"text","text":">("},{"text":"mutex","kind":"externalParam"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"MutexT"},{"kind":"text","text":")"}],"roleHeading":"Instance Method","modules":[{"name":"GLib"}],"extendedModule":"GLib"},"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Cond\/wait(mutex:)"},"abstract":[{"text":"Atomically releases ","type":"text"},{"code":"mutex","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" and waits until ","type":"text"},{"code":"cond","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" is signalled.","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"When this function returns, "},{"code":"mutex","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" is locked again and owned by the","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"calling thread.","type":"text"}],"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"platforms":["macOS"],"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"wait"},{"kind":"text","text":"<"},{"text":"MutexT","kind":"genericParameter"},{"kind":"text","text":">("},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"mutex"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"text":"MutexT","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":") ","kind":"text"},{"text":"where","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"MutexT"},{"text":" : ","kind":"text"},{"text":"MutexProtocol","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/MutexProtocol","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:4GLib13MutexProtocolP"}]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"kind":"content","content":[{"text":"Discussion","level":2,"type":"heading","anchor":"discussion"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"When using condition variables, it is possible that a spurious wakeup"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"may occur (ie: "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_cond_wait()"},{"text":" returns even though ","type":"text"},{"code":"g_cond_signal()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" was","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"not called).  It’s also possible that a stolen wakeup may occur."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"This is when ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_cond_signal()"},{"type":"text","text":" is called, but another thread acquires"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"code":"mutex","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" before this thread and modifies the state of the program in"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"such a way that when "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_cond_wait()"},{"text":" is able to return, the expected","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"condition is no longer met.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"For this reason, ","type":"text"},{"code":"g_cond_wait()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" must always be used in a loop.  See"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"the documentation for ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Cond"},{"type":"text","text":" for a complete example."}]}]}],"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"patch":0,"major":0},"kind":"symbol","sections":[],"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/glib\/cond\/wait(mutex:)"]}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Cond","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Cond\/CondProtocol-Implementations"]]},"references":{"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/Cond":{"fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"class"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identi